<paragraph blockId="2.[113,752,637,854]" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">
Alphonse 
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards A" box="[222,518,637,661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="229 - 267" refId="ref8782" refString="Milne-Edwards A (1872) Recherches sur la faune carcinologique de la Nouvelle-Caledonie. Nouvelles Archives du Museum d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, 8: 229 - 267, pls. 10 - 14." type="journal article" year="1872">Milne-Edwards (1872: 234)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[638,751,638,661]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis box="[638,651,638,661]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[664,751,638,661]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only a more spiny variant of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="H. Milne Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[470,573,670,693]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspera">
<emphasis box="[470,483,670,693]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[500,573,670,693]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">aspera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and as such, it has generally been considered by subsequent authors to be a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="H. Milne Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[451,551,734,757]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspera">
<emphasis box="[451,464,734,757]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[478,551,734,757]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">aspera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Ward M" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="49 - 113" refId="ref10086" refString="Ward M (1942) Notes on the Crustacea of the Desjardins Museum, Mauritius Institute, with descriptions of new genera and species. Bulletin of the Mauritius Institute, 2 (2): 49 - 113, pls. 5, 6." type="book chapter" year="1942">Ward, 1942: 74</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Griffin DJG &amp; Tranter HA" box="[156,472,765,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 335" refId="ref7911" refString="Griffin DJG &amp; Tranter HA (1986) The Decapoda Brachyura of the Siboga expedition. Part VIII: Majidae. Siboga Expeditie Monografie, 39: [i-vii], 1 - 335, pls. 1 - 22, 3 tables." type="book chapter" year="1986">Griffin &amp; Tranter, 1986: 244</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng PKL &amp; Davie PJF" box="[485,747,765,790]" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="369 - 384" refId="ref9081" refString="Ng PKL &amp; Davie PJF (2002) A checklist of the Brachyuran crabs of Phuket and western Thailand. Phuket Marine Biological Center Special Publication, 23 (2): 369 - 384." type="journal article" year="2002">Ng &amp; Davie, 2002: 371</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng PKL &amp; Guinot D &amp; Davie PJF" box="[113,332,797,822]" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref9117" refString="Ng PKL, Guinot D &amp; Davie PJF (2008) Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 17: 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">Ng et al., 2008: 118</bibRefCitation>
). We follow this classification pending a taxonomic revision of the genus.
</paragraph>
